you've accomplished

01:56.633 --> 01:59.267
is getting arrested
for being an idiot.

01:59.367 --> 02:02.067
Is that what you want
your legacy to be?

02:02.133 --> 02:03.267
And you,

02:03.367 --> 02:05.400
you look like every other

02:05.500 --> 02:08.067
self-centered,
dope-smoking kid with your--

02:08.133 --> 02:11.800
with your cool T-shirt
and your pervert mustache.

02:11.900 --> 02:13.500
- I look weird without it,
but thank you

02:13.600 --> 02:14.900
for the compliment
on the T-shirt.

02:15.067 --> 02:16.133
That's very sweet of you.

02:16.233 --> 02:17.367
- When was the last time

02:17.467 --> 02:18.767
you did something
for someone else

02:18.867 --> 02:21.300
rather than smoking
that damn hashish?

02:21.400 --> 02:24.800
And you, you look like

02:24.900 --> 02:27.433
you could actually be
an upstanding citizen.

02:27.533 --> 02:28.800
- Thank you.

02:28.900 --> 02:30.567
- What do you want to do
with your life, son?

02:30.667 --> 02:34.167
- Uh, well, sir, one day
I hope to be city councilman.

02:34.267 --> 02:36.500
- Well, there's a war
on drugs out there,

02:36.600 --> 02:38.767
and you're on
the wrong side of it.

02:38.867 --> 02:40.633
I want the three of you

02:40.733 --> 02:43.067
to go to a
Narcotics Anonymous meeting,

02:43.167 --> 02:46.467
and perhaps getting
a firsthand look at how drugs

02:46.567 --> 02:50.267
rip people's lives apart
will do you some good.

02:50.367 --> 02:53.100
- Thank you,
honorable Judge "Browntown."

02:54.500 --> 02:55.633
- Judge, I just
want you to know

02:55.733 --> 02:56.900
I'm gonna
take full advantage

02:57.067 --> 02:58.400
of these N.A. classes.

02:58.500 --> 03:00.733
- Well, I'm glad
to hear that, son.

03:00.833 --> 03:02.167
- Yeah, I'm gonna go undercover

03:02.267 --> 03:04.133
and sniff out some
primo intel for you.

03:04.233 --> 03:06.633
Hopefully we can put
an end to this Rancho drug war

03:06.733 --> 03:08.300
once and for all, right?

03:08.400 --> 03:11.267
- Do not do that.

03:11.367 --> 03:13.267
- Right...
side of the law.

03:13.367 --> 03:15.100
I'm doing it, yeah.
- No, don't.

03:15.200 --> 03:16.800
- [sighs]
I need to smoke some weed.

03:16.900 --> 03:19.433
- Court-mandated meetings,
am I right?

03:19.533 --> 03:21.100
What are you in for, bud?

03:21.200 --> 03:23.767
- Ah, I'm actually just
observing the meeting.

03:23.867 --> 03:25.067
I'm a journalist.

03:25.167 --> 03:27.067
- Oh, well,
I dream journal, so--

03:27.133 --> 03:30.733
- No, I'm--I'm a reporter
for "VICE" magazine.

03:30.833 --> 03:33.967
I'm writing a story
about meth abuse.

03:34.067 --> 03:36.467
To be perfectly honest,
I'm looking for an addict

03:36.567 --> 03:38.767
that would agree
to be profiled.

03:38.867 --> 03:40.100
See you guys in the meeting.

03:40.200 --> 03:42.533
[gentle chimes playing]

03:42.633 --> 03:44.267
- Yes, you will.

03:46.200 --> 03:47.367
- Got a large group tonight.

03:47.467 --> 03:49.367
- Whoo!
Yeah, recovery!

03:49.467 --> 03:51.067
- Welcome, my name's Tim,

03:51.167 --> 03:52.967
and, uh, when I first
walked through the doors--

03:53.067 --> 03:54.867
- Dude, I just figured out

03:54.967 --> 03:58.200
what I'm gonna do to, like,
have my legacy be badass.

03:58.300 --> 04:02.633
My face on the cover
of "VICE" magazine.

04:02.733 --> 04:05.067
- Oh, yeah, yeah,
yeah, yeah.

04:05.100 --> 04:06.233
But the only thing is,

04:06.333 --> 04:07.633
is that guy wants
a crazy meth head.

04:07.733 --> 04:08.867
- Mm-hmm.

04:08.967 --> 04:10.400
- You just occasionally
smoke weed.

04:10.500 --> 04:12.067
- Except for every day
and at night, also.

04:12.167 --> 04:14.267
- Yeah, I'm just saying,
all you've ever done is weed

04:14.367 --> 04:16.600
and, you know,
beer and mushrooms

04:16.700 --> 04:19.367
and acid and, you know,
ecstasy, Molly...

04:19.467 --> 04:20.833
- Mm-hmm, yeah.
- Some lean, sizzurp.

04:20.933 --> 04:23.200
- Yep.
- But other than that...

04:23.300 --> 04:24.533
- Did you say something?

04:24.633 --> 04:26.067
Would you like
to come up and share?

04:26.133 --> 04:27.900
- I'm--I'm cool.
I'm not an addict.

04:28.067 --> 04:29.433
- [scoffs]
Okay.

04:29.533 --> 04:31.100
If that's what
your heart believes.

04:31.200 --> 04:32.433
- Come on!

04:32.533 --> 04:34.433
I don't have
a problem, okay?

04:34.533 --> 04:35.933
I'm fine!

04:36.067 --> 04:37.900
Can we go, please?
I need to smoke a bowl.

04:38.067 --> 04:39.567
- No, I'm gonna stay here.
I have work to do.

04:39.667 --> 04:40.833
- Okay, yeah,
I gotta go.

04:40.933 --> 04:43.433
I gotta get some fresh air
really quick.

04:43.533 --> 04:46.433
[chill music]

04:46.533 --> 04:48.100
*

04:48.200 --> 04:50.100
- Dang, what's up
with all these snacks?

04:50.200 --> 04:51.733
[awkward laugh]

04:53.167 --> 04:54.333
What's up, man?
I'm Shaunders.

04:54.433 --> 04:55.700
Good to meet you, dude.

04:55.800 --> 04:57.167
Can you believe
these marks in there?

04:57.267 --> 04:59.667
Talking about,
"I wanna get high."

04:59.767 --> 05:01.567
"I wish I was still high."

05:01.667 --> 05:03.233
[bleep], go get high!

05:03.333 --> 05:04.800
Know what I mean?
But I'll tell you what.

05:04.900 --> 05:06.267
I, uh, probably
gonna need something

05:06.367 --> 05:07.933
a little stronger
than this coffee

05:08.067 --> 05:10.233
if I'ma get through this
meeting; for real, though.

05:10.333 --> 05:12.367
Do you have a hookup?

05:12.467 --> 05:14.800
- Are you seriously asking me
for drugs at a N.A. meeting?

05:14.900 --> 05:16.333
- Did I stutter?

05:16.433 --> 05:18.900
- Dude, I've been sober
for eight months.

05:19.067 --> 05:20.800
- Oh, you gonna take it
personal, okay.

05:20.900 --> 05:22.633
Please, man, you look
like a old-ass,

05:22.733 --> 05:24.933
whack Peter Pan,
so, like, [buzzes].

05:27.067 --> 05:28.333
- Hey, "fyi,"

05:28.433 --> 05:30.800
normally what I say here,
I want to stay here,

05:30.900 --> 05:33.733
but if any of this lands
in "VICE" magazine...

05:35.733 --> 05:37.400
- I'm actually
looking for someone

05:37.500 --> 05:40.567
who's in the grip of addiction,
struggling to get out.

05:40.667 --> 05:42.467
You seem like you're getting
your life together.

05:42.567 --> 05:44.067
Linda:
My name is Linda.

05:44.167 --> 05:47.300
I went to that bar,
Ed's Jug House, to score,

05:47.400 --> 05:50.400
and I left my kids
alone in the car.

05:50.500 --> 05:52.533
Social Services
took them from me,

05:52.633 --> 05:55.867
and now I just want
to see my kids again.

05:55.967 --> 05:57.633
[crying]

05:57.733 --> 05:59.400
- [crying]

05:59.500 --> 06:01.933
Oh, God!

06:02.067 --> 06:04.067
Oh, you could sit down,
'cause that actually--

06:04.167 --> 06:06.367
sit down right now--
'cause that inspired me.

06:06.467 --> 06:09.600
I recently lost myself
to meth once again,

06:09.700 --> 06:12.133
and just like this girl
who seems like

06:12.233 --> 06:14.767
she has it all together now

06:14.867 --> 06:17.433
and is fully
on the road to recovery,

06:17.533 --> 06:19.367
I was also at Ed's Jug House,

06:19.467 --> 06:21.433
and I...

06:21.533 --> 06:23.200
I ate a puppy.

06:23.300 --> 06:25.367
And on top
of that, I, uh...

06:25.467 --> 06:27.433
sucked a bunch of [bleep].

06:27.533 --> 06:29.100
I'm good at it,
so I could just

06:29.200 --> 06:30.433
really get in there
and just...

06:30.533 --> 06:32.167
[gagging]

06:32.267 --> 06:35.433
Big ones, small ones,
girthy ones,

06:35.533 --> 06:38.533
ones that looked like
it had, like, alopecia.

06:38.633 --> 06:40.967
And that's my story.

06:44.267 --> 06:48.100
[chill music]

06:48.200 --> 06:49.467
- Did I miss anything?

06:49.567 --> 06:51.133
Psych!
I hate this shit.

06:51.233 --> 06:52.700
I'm out the game.
It's been a long time.

06:52.800 --> 06:54.367
I'm trying to hop back in,
so I'm wondering

06:54.467 --> 06:56.167
if you got any connects.

06:56.267 --> 06:59.533
- It ain't smart to be
asking questions about Zippo.

06:59.633 --> 07:01.867
- Zip--Zippo?
You say Zippo?

07:01.967 --> 07:04.400
You tell Zippo...

07:04.500 --> 07:06.600
Shaunders.

07:08.800 --> 07:10.300
- Just need a smoke, man.

07:10.400 --> 07:12.333
Jeez, get off my back.

07:14.833 --> 07:17.267
- I can't--I can't--
I can't do this.

07:17.367 --> 07:18.933
- Mr. Buckley?

07:19.067 --> 07:20.167
- Yeah--no.

07:20.267 --> 07:21.633
- [laughing]
It is you!

07:21.733 --> 07:23.067
- What?
Oh, hi.

07:23.167 --> 07:25.067
- Wow, Mr. Buckley, hey.
- Can I help you?

07:25.100 --> 07:26.900
- I haven't seen you
since drama camp.

07:27.067 --> 07:29.300
It's me, it's Blake Henderson.
- Oh, yes.

07:29.400 --> 07:32.633
- I, uh, I was Lenny's, uh,
understudy's backup's stand-in.

07:32.733 --> 07:34.367
- Okay, yes, yeah,
and you were wonderful.

07:34.467 --> 07:36.167
Wonderful performance.
- What are you doing?

07:36.267 --> 07:38.467
You, uh, going--
going into the meeting, or...?

07:38.567 --> 07:40.967
- I just can't seem
to drag myself in there.

07:41.067 --> 07:43.433
They're such dreaded affairs,
aren't they?

07:43.533 --> 07:46.167
- Well, now that I
have you here,

07:46.267 --> 07:48.833
I'd love to just pick your brain
about acting, right?

07:48.933 --> 07:50.600
Get it--just write it
in my little notebook.

07:50.700 --> 07:51.833
- Well, write this down.

07:51.933 --> 07:53.100
- All right.

07:53.200 --> 07:54.100
- "Give it up."

07:54.200 --> 07:55.667
- What, you quit?

07:55.767 --> 07:57.733
I mean, you're like,
basically the main reason

07:57.833 --> 08:00.700
I am an actor, I mean,

08:00.800 --> 08:02.333
ever since I saw
the play you wrote,

08:02.433 --> 08:04.633
uh, "McBreath."

08:04.733 --> 08:06.833
- I curse you,
Jen D'Angelo.

08:06.933 --> 08:08.500
- Yeah!
- Yes, I wrote it, yeah.

08:08.600 --> 08:10.567
Um, I'm afraid there was
a little bit of an incident

08:10.667 --> 08:13.133
at my last run of
"Hedwig and the Angry Inch"

08:13.233 --> 08:14.600
at the Rancho Playhouse.

08:14.700 --> 08:15.733
And I really don't
want to talk about it,

08:15.833 --> 08:16.767
but it was good
to see you.

08:16.867 --> 08:18.267
- Oh, my gosh, what happened?

08:18.367 --> 08:19.267
I know you don't want
to talk about it,

08:19.367 --> 08:20.533
but what happened?

08:20.633 --> 08:22.067
- Several of the actors refused

08:22.133 --> 08:24.900
to call me by
my character's name offstage,

08:25.067 --> 08:28.400
which,
for a method actor as I am--

08:28.500 --> 08:29.800
that was unacceptable.

08:29.900 --> 08:31.233
- Oh, right.
- I wound up...

08:31.333 --> 08:34.200
striking several
of those children...

08:34.300 --> 08:35.600
repeatedly.

08:35.700 --> 08:36.967
- Oh, that's dumb.

08:37.067 --> 08:38.233
- Yeah, I know, I--

08:38.333 --> 08:39.900
- I mean, of the kids.

08:40.067 --> 08:43.200
- Yes, and then of course once
acting was taken away from me,

08:43.300 --> 08:44.900
I turned to drugs.

08:45.067 --> 08:46.700
They were the only thing
that gave me that high

08:46.800 --> 08:49.400
that once, the stage gave me.

08:49.500 --> 08:52.700
- You know, I want
to do you a favor.

08:52.800 --> 08:53.933
- Thank you.

08:54.067 --> 08:55.267
- All right.
Excuse me, Linda--

08:55.367 --> 08:57.133
- No, hey, hey!
Hey, so you probably

08:57.233 --> 08:58.867
want to write that article
about me, right?

08:58.967 --> 09:01.333
After you heard the shocking
and scandalous tale

09:01.433 --> 09:04.133
that I just...spoke upon?

09:04.233 --> 09:06.300
- Actually, Linda's story
spoke to me a lot.

09:06.400 --> 09:07.867
- Linda's did?
- Yeah.

09:07.967 --> 09:09.267
- But she didn't suck

09:09.367 --> 09:11.167
a ton of little [bleep]
in her story.

09:11.267 --> 09:12.433
- Yeah, listen, Adam,

09:12.533 --> 09:13.867
you seem a little
thick in the middle

09:13.967 --> 09:15.433
for a meth addict,
to be honest with you.

09:15.533 --> 09:17.200
- Okay, well, this is
a safe place, so shut up.

09:17.300 --> 09:18.600
- I gotta talk to Linda.

09:18.700 --> 09:21.067
- Oh, God.

09:21.100 --> 09:22.567
- What are you doing?
- Oh, God!

09:22.667 --> 09:24.700
Oh, your hateful words!
It's a trigger.

09:24.800 --> 09:26.900
It's a--it's a trigger for me,
and I'm gonna go do meth.

09:27.067 --> 09:28.767
- Okay, I'm sorry.

09:28.867 --> 09:30.233
Did I upset you that much?

09:30.333 --> 09:32.167
- Nothing that
a little meth won't fix,

09:32.267 --> 09:34.433
and that's what I'm gonna
go do right now.

09:34.533 --> 09:36.500
Bye-bye, Linda.
I'm doing meth.

09:36.600 --> 09:37.500
- Okay, I'm gonna go.

09:37.600 --> 09:38.733
- Actually, Adam,

09:38.833 --> 09:40.367
would you mind
if I follow along?

09:40.467 --> 09:42.167
If you're gonna do meth,
I actually would like

09:42.267 --> 09:43.700
to get a firsthand
look at that if you--

09:43.800 --> 09:45.200
you don't mind
me shadowing you.

09:45.300 --> 09:47.233
- So you want to do
the article about me?

09:47.333 --> 09:49.567
- I mean, maybe--
- Yes!

09:49.667 --> 09:51.200
Yeah, okay, come on.

09:51.300 --> 09:52.433
Let's ride.

09:52.533 --> 09:54.067
My condolences
for your children.

09:54.133 --> 09:55.267
That was a sad story.

09:55.367 --> 09:57.067
Mine was more sad, though.
Whoo!

09:57.100 --> 09:59.067
