Come on.

10:11.067 --> 10:13.233
- Guys, I'm sorry,
but you can't be in here.

10:13.333 --> 10:15.567
We've got rehearsal
in about five minutes.

10:15.667 --> 10:17.933
- And I need but four, okay?

10:18.033 --> 10:19.900
This is Mr. Buckley,

10:20.000 --> 10:21.967
Rancho Cucamonga acting legend.

10:22.067 --> 10:23.833
Have you heard of him?
- No.

10:23.933 --> 10:25.933
- Well, we would like to
perform a scene from his play,

10:26.033 --> 10:27.433
which I'm sure
you've heard of,

10:27.533 --> 10:29.067
"McBreath."

10:29.167 --> 10:30.300
- Fine.

10:30.400 --> 10:32.133
- Excellent.
[laughs]

10:32.233 --> 10:33.400
- Wh--wh--what are you doing?

10:33.500 --> 10:35.100
- All right, everybody.

10:35.200 --> 10:38.333
Um, I will be playing
the role of Angela,

10:38.433 --> 10:42.500
and he shall be playing
the role of McBreath, our hero.

10:42.600 --> 10:45.233
Our scene starts
in a crowded bus.

10:45.333 --> 10:47.467
Angela enters.

10:47.567 --> 10:50.000
[as Angela]
Excuse me, pardon me.

10:50.100 --> 10:51.667
- Blake, I can't do this.

10:51.767 --> 10:53.000
- Oh, excuse me, pardon me.

10:53.100 --> 10:55.033
- I can't do this without drugs.

10:55.133 --> 10:57.067
- Excuse me!

10:57.167 --> 10:59.700
Excuse me.

11:01.567 --> 11:04.467
- Here, take my seat.

11:04.567 --> 11:06.900
- Oh, you are too kind.

11:07.067 --> 11:08.400
I'm Angela.

11:08.500 --> 11:11.133
- I'm Leonard, Angela,

11:11.233 --> 11:13.767
but everyone calls me McBreath.

11:13.867 --> 11:15.933
- McBreath?

11:16.067 --> 11:19.933
- In seventh grade,
we played spin the bottle,

11:20.067 --> 11:22.967
and it landed
on Jen D'Angelo.

11:23.067 --> 11:24.933
We kissed, and then she told me

11:25.067 --> 11:29.200
my breath smelled like
McDonald's cheeseburgers.

11:29.300 --> 11:30.900
Then she got everyone

11:31.067 --> 11:35.367
